Dancer-Session-Storable

A module for the Dancer web framework to provide session storage using data
serialised using Storable and written to files.

For usage, see:
  Dancer::Session, for details on how to use sessions within Dancer
  Dancer, for the Dancer web framework


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Dancer::Session::Storable

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Dancer-Session-Storable

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Dancer-Session-Storable

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Dancer-Session-Storable

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Dancer-Session-Storable/


